 @f7y8u9ugf  I think I'm (still) better communicating with non-developers to figure out what's actually needed. I've communicated enough with non-developers to know that "normal people" cannot formulate their needs or ideas clearly and figuring that out and filling in blanks from the context (real world) still seems too hard to do for an AI.

I do believe that software architects will be replaced by AI in the long run but I would assume that's nearly the last occupations that AI can successfully do.

Human psychology is a field in general that will be hard to tackle with the current AI designs. However, the rules for psychology are less strict than for writing software so "good enough" may be easier to achieve there. There are still too many unknowns to say anything for sure, though.
